The worst drought to hit the United States since 1895, when record keeping began, has 
damaged grain crops in the major grain growing states and could lead to food shortages 
in poorer nations. The drought has forced some states to import hay from other states. 
Communities in many states have imposed tight water rationing.</SUM>
